dge ’s decision could affect an estimated 100 to 200 people who were detained upon arrival at American airports . Judge Ann M. Donnelly of Federal District Court in Brooklyn who was nominated by former President Barack Obama ruled just before 9 p. m. that implementing Mr. Trump ’s order by sending the travelers home could cause them “ irreparable harm . ” She said the government was “ enjoined and restrained from
